main event: On 26 March 1959, three military personnel at Biggs A.F.B., Texas, sighted a round metallic object moving rapidly across the sky, emitting a whining sound.
interesting points: The object moved about 25 degrees in 9 seconds with no visible trail or exhaust., All witnesses were military personnel on duty., The object was described as shiny and round., The sound associated with the object was like a high-pitched hum., The sighting lasted for 9 seconds.
